h1 Buttons

p Buttons should be used to denote something that performs an action on a page.

section.styleguide-module-details
  h2 Primary Buttons

  h3 Usage
  dl.styleguide-usage
    dt Creating a Primary Button
    dd Primary buttons are used to denote the primary action on a form or page. Any HTML element can have the appearance of a primary button by adding the class #{inline_code(".button-primary")}.
    dt Recommended Elements
    dd The #{inline_code("button")} and #{inline_code("a")} elements are the preferred elements to use when creating a button. They are easier to style consistently across multiple browsers. The #{inline_code("input")} element may also be used as a buttom but it's more restrictive in how it can be styled.
    dt Alternative Smaller Button
    dd In some cases the interface requires a smaller button. The #{inline_code(".button-primary-small")} class is available as a replacement.
